<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#D0BC90">Originally posted by Arhu on 06-28-2001 07:29 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Aye, Dar, that's true for MUDs even more than for any other game. And due to the fact that  :div: is no MUD (yet?), they have all the time they need to get the balancing right.  :)

Wyll: Yeah, in the end, it's all about nerfing. As I said I'm normally not against late balancing, but at the same time I can understand the frustration of dismayed players. D2 is a special case, I remember how long it took me to reach Lvl. 34 (where I stopped) with my bowazon, and can scarcely imagine how much time real players have invested in developing their characters. Nerfing the general public is quite ok, cos they wouldn't really notice it (assuming relatively low level characters), nerfing the loyal fanbase without any kind of compensation, however, is [i]bad[/i]. Blizzard was a little too harsh, imo. Continuously beating your own, most loving children is for sure going to backfire someday.

Oh, they can move the topic, but they have to bring themselves to do that first, so I don't think it will happen.  ;)

[i]Meow...[/i]
Arhu</TEXTAREA>
